  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Inscription on a Desk
  author: Kim Il-son
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Stacked high upon you:
    the classics and histories,
    the deeds of the wise and the works of the sage.

    Leaning against you, I dream:
    of Fu Xi, of the Duke of Zhou.

    Your substance is wood, unadorned—
    I wish to be like you.
    Quiet you stand, yet boundless your purpose.
    Morning and evening, I face you,
    this old man and his weathered companion.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: Fu Xi (希皇) and the Duke of Zhou (周公) represent idealized models of virtuous rulership in Chinese tradition—the legendary sage-king and the exemplary minister-prince respectively.
  - key: ''
    value: This inscription celebrates the desk as both repository of wisdom through texts and mirror for the author's own aspiration toward humble integrity.
